namespace Java.Lang.Reflect

Contains .NET proxy types for Java classes from the package java.lang.reflect.

See:
          Description

Type Summary
AccessibleObject .NET proxy type for class java.lang.reflect.AccessibleObject.
The AccessibleObject class is the base class for Field, Method and Constructor objects.
AnnotatedElement .NET proxy type for interface java.lang.reflect.AnnotatedElement.
Represents an annotated element of the program currently running in this VM.
AnnotatedType .NET proxy type for interface java.lang.reflect.AnnotatedType.
AnnotatedType represents the potentially annotated use of a type in the program currently running in this VM.
Constructor .NET proxy type for class java.lang.reflect.Constructor.
Constructor provides information about, and access to, a single constructor for a class.
Executable .NET proxy type for class java.lang.reflect.Executable.
A shared superclass for the common functionality of Java.Lang.Reflect.Method and Java.Lang.Reflect.Constructor.
Field .NET proxy type for class java.lang.reflect.Field.
A Field provides information about, and dynamic access to, a single field of a class or an interface.
GenericDeclaration .NET proxy type for interface java.lang.reflect.GenericDeclaration.
A common interface for all entities that declare type variables.
Member .NET proxy type for interface java.lang.reflect.Member.
Member is an interface that reflects identifying information about a single member (a field or a method) or a constructor.
Method .NET proxy type for class java.lang.reflect.Method.
A Method provides information about, and access to, a single method on a class or interface.
Type .NET proxy type for interface java.lang.reflect.Type.
TypeVariable .NET proxy type for interface java.lang.reflect.TypeVariable.
TypeVariable is the common superinterface for type variables of kinds.
